From: Jan Grulich <jgrulich@redhat.com>
Date: Tue, 31 Mar 2026 15:05:00 +0000
Subject: Bug 2023103 - WebRTC backport: PipeWire capture: fix camera
 capability enumeration race and duplicates r=pehrsons

Don't enumerate capabilities without actual format changes. Push the new
discovered capabilities into a pending list and swap pending list into
actual capabilities only after all params from the enumeration have been
received to ensure capabilities are never empty while enumerating.

This is a simple backport of an WebRTC upstream change.

Upstream commit: 4487631837501e9ff44195f4a718f0b743c8e5d9

Differential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D290868
Mercurial Revision: https://hg.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/rev/a905d52a7522c83288771bdd918cac0b4c8143d4
